attestNAV(uint256,uint256,bytes32).details: When threshold > 1, this creates/signs a pending attestation      When threshold = 1, this directly applies the NAV (backwards compatible)

params.totalAssets: Total T-Bill value in USD (18 decimals)

returns.annualizedBps: Estimated annualized yield in basis points
returns.periodDays: Number of days in calculation period

returns.maxNav: Maximum NAV per share that can be attested

params.count: Number of historical reports to return

returns.reports: Array of NAV reports in range

returns.previousNav: Previous NAV per share (or current if no history)

returns.isFresh: True if NAV is within staleness period

returns.isActive: Whether there's an active pending attestation

returns.overdue: True if NAV is stale (exceeds maxStalenessSeconds)

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

returns.seconds_: Time elapsed since last NAV update

setAttestationThreshold(uint256).details: Threshold cannot exceed current attestor count

params.threshold_: Number of attestors required (1 = single-sig, >1 = multi-sig)

setAuthorizedAttestor(address,bool).details: Updates attestorCount for multi-sig threshold validation

setMaxNavChangeBps(uint256).details: Must be between 10 bps (0.1%) and 1000 bps (10%)

params.seconds_: New staleness period (must be between 1 hour and 7 days)

params.expiry_: Time in seconds before pending attestation expires (min 1 hour, max 24 hours)

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

DEFAULT_MAX_NAV_CHANGE_BPS().notice: Default maximum NAV change per attestation (5%)

attestationThreshold().notice: Minimum attestors required to finalize NAV (threshold)

getAnnualizedYield().notice: Calculate annualized yield based on history

getCumulativeYield(uint256).notice: Get cumulative yield since a baseline

getHistoricalNAV(uint256).notice: Get NAV at specific historical index

getHistoryLength().notice: Get number of historical NAV reports

getMaxAllowedNavChange().notice: Calculate the maximum NAV value allowed for next attestation

getNAVHistoryInRange(uint256,uint256).notice: Get NAV reports within a date range

hasAttested(bytes32,address).notice: Track which attestors have signed which pending attestation

hasAttestorSigned(address).notice: Check if an attestor has signed the current pending attestation

isNAVFresh().notice: Check if NAV is fresh (not stale)

maxNavChangeBps().notice: Configurable maximum NAV change per attestation (in basis points)

pendingAttestationExpiry().notice: Expiry time for pending attestations (default 4 hours)

pendingAttestations(bytes32).notice: Current pending attestation (keyed by hash of attestation data)

setMaxNavChangeBps(uint256).notice: Set maximum NAV change per attestation
